title: Meet the new Love Island Australia intruders Anna, 27, and Phoebe, 28
text:
Two sexy intruders are set to shake things up on Love Island Australia.

Bikini bombshells Anna, 27, and Phoebe, 28, will enter the Fijian villa on Wednesday night's episode.

Anna, a model from Melbourne, said she has dated her fair share of 'douche bags' in past, so knows exactly what she wants in a boyfriend.

Meet the new Love Island intruders! Bikini bombshells Anna (left) and Phoebe (right) are getting ready to shake up the villa - and they're 'not afraid' to split couples

'I've definitely dated my fair share of douche bags in my time,' Anna said. 'I'm looking for someone who is nice and who doesn't lie or cheat.'

Meanwhile, Phoebe is a credit analyst from Sydney and isn't afraid to speak her mind.

'I'm fiery and outspoken and am known for having a temper,' she said. 'I know what I want and I'm not afraid to go for it!'

'I'm fiery and outspoken': Phoebe, a credit analyst from Sydney, isn't afraid to speak her mind

She know what she wants! 'I've definitely dated my fair share of douche bags in my time,' Anna said. 'I'm looking for someone who is nice and who doesn't lie or cheat'

It comes after Love Island fans were left shocked by Cartier Surjan, 19, revealing on Tuesday that she wants to 'find a husband' and even has a list of baby names.

'Just a quick reminder that Cartier is nineteen years old and that is too young,' one viewer tweeted.

Another wrote: 'Oh, [shut the f**k up]. Talking about baby names makes you sound like a bloody idiot.'

Say what? It comes after Love Island fans were left shocked by Cartier Surjan (pictured) revealing on Tuesday that she wants to 'find a husband' and even has a list of baby names

Questions about Cartier's age were raised on both Twitter and Instagram, with fans saying she needs more life experience before settling down.

Meanwhile, intruders like Anna and Phoebe will continue to arrive at the villa throughout the course of the series.

Love Island Australia continues Wednesday at 8:40pm on Channel Nine
